snippet.textDisplay:
A lot of people have ideas but fight is a game of chess, you can’t do just any moves because you like to, you have to see what your opponent does, who ever has the sharper mind will be victorious. You constantly have to be aware of your and your opponent’s position and have many options to transition to not just one option and hope that he does what you want so you can capitalize on it. It doesn’t work like that.
You have to have at least three scenarios at any given time if not more to be a great fighter. Otherwise you are just average.
just my two cents

snippet.textDisplay: Yeah i agree Chael. One thing that’s always been great about each time these guys are going to fight is that Tony has never looked intimidated, he’s always has had the same calmness after having to study Khabib. So yeah , it’s because he’s spent his life having answers for this particular opponent, he doesn’t see him as the scary champ because he’s stood in his face long before that. Tony knows he’s the guy who can stop 3-4 of the things that Khabib has to do to get to that place of control and to throw a monkey wrench of surprise. Tony also is a master on his back and the master of these surprise squirrelly moves that leave people in shock/frustrated for a second. If Khabib gets frustrated he’s done, if he is stopped in his steps of the ingredients he needs to do what he always does then he becomes prey for Tony. Tony is winning a lot and is doing all sorts of different stuff and we will see more because he has answers for this opponent. There’s no better opponent for Tony for the belt than Khabib —Tony is designed for this. He also has a slight height advantage which I’ve always believed is 1 advantage anyone has along with any grappling skills on Khabib. And we know that is why Khabib cuts 3 divisions-he won’t dare go up against taller guys because wrapping the legs and reaching the face won’t work. I honestly think Khabib would be easy for Diaz standing and on the ground.  I believe Tony shuts Khabib down and i also think Conor would take the rematch. You don’t have to be an amazing grappler to beat him. Striking can take out a grappler. We forget Ronda , but Rondas head wasn’t in it either. She got stopped by 2 strikers but, then Meisha goes and beats Holly, we know Ronda beat Meisha oh yeah twice! And off the top of my head there were at least 2 opponents who beat Amanda that Ronda beat. So point is Tony has everything you would need to be Khabib and yeah you can be a great striker and take out a great grappler and that will be Conor if Tony doesn’t do it. Bye Bye Khabib hide location!

And we know that is why Khabib cuts 3 divisions-he won’t dare go up against taller guys because wrapping the legs and reaching the face won’t work. I honestly think Khabib would be easy for Diaz standing and on the ground.  I believe Tony shuts Khabib down and i also think Conor would take the rematch. You don’t have to be an amazing grappler to beat him. Striking can take out a grappler. We forget Ronda , but Rondas head wasn’t in it either. She got stopped by 2 strikers but, then Meisha goes and beats Holly, we know Ronda beat Meisha oh yeah twice! And off the top of my head there were at least 2 opponents who beat Amanda that Ronda beat. So point is Tony has everything you would need to be Khabib and yeah you can be a great striker and take out a great grappler and that will be Conor if Tony doesn’t do it. Bye Bye Khabib hide location!
